        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &amp;quot;Additional Financial Assistance for the Children of Persons Engaged in the Cleaning Profession&amp;quot; scheme was launched by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department, Government of Rajasthan. The scheme provides an additional financial assistance of ₹500/- per month to children of individuals working in the cleaning or sanitation profession. This assistance is given to students already receiving a scholarship under the Post-Matric Scholarship Scheme, ensuring their continued education.\n",
        "benefits_md": "**Financial Assistance:** \n\n  - This scheme provides ₹500/- per month as additional financial assistance to children of individuals working in the cleaning/sanitation profession.\n\n**Note:** Assistance will be provided for a maximum of 10 months per year.\n",
        "briefDescription": "This scheme aims to provide additional financial assistance of ₹500/- per month to children of individuals working in cleaning/sanitation profession. This assistance is given to students already receiving a scholarship under Post-Matric Scholarship Scheme, ensuring their continued education.",
